\":\"**Ensuring class loading coverage**\\n\\nI need a successful path for `loadClass` to ensure that `ClassLoader#loadClass` gets covered. It seems we require both tests—one for a normal loader (where `loadClass` succeeds) and another for a fallback path using `forName`. \\n\\nBut I should consider resetting counters only for the fallback. The dynamic report indicates that `ClassLoader#loadClass` might remain uncovered if failures don’t count. If the first normal invocation hits `RAFile` and returns, it could prevent `Class.forName` from being triggered. Then the fallback hidden would need to hit that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_01JN2tI43rISxOxXiENdZ1U1|fc_031b564316a0b7fd016a116b937138819192339b43e15ab69e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RAFileTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(classHidingLoader);\n\n            try (Connection connection = openConnection(url); Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n                Database database = databaseSession(connection).getDatabase();\n                byte[] expectedBlock = \"0123456789abcdef\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII);\n                LobStoreRAFile lobStore = new LobStoreRAFile(database, expectedBlock.length);\n\n                InMemoryRandomAccessStorage.resetObservations();\n                classHidingLoader.reset();\n\n                lobStore.setBlockBytes(expectedBlock, 0, 1);\n\n                assertThat(lobStore.getBlockBytes(0, 1)).isEqualTo(expectedBlock);\n                lobStore.close();\n\n                statement.execute(\"SHUTDOWN\");\n            }\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n", "newText": "        try (Connection connection = openConnection(url); Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n            Database database = databaseSession(connection).getDatabase();\n            byte[] expectedBlock = \"0123456789abcdef\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII);\n\n            writeAndReadLobBlock(database, expectedBlock);\n\n            InMemoryRandomAccessStorage.resetObservations();\n            classHidingLoader.reset();\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(classHidingLoader);\n\n            writeAndReadLobBlock(database, expectedBlock);\n\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n            statement.execute(\"SHUTDOWN\");\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\n        }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static Connection openConnection(String url) throws Exception {\n        JDBCDataSource dataSource = new JDBCDataSource();\n\n        dataSource.setUrl(url);\n        dataSource.setUser(\"SA\");\n        dataSource.setPassword(\"\");\n\n        return dataSource.getConnection();\n    }\n\n    private static Session databaseSession(Connection connection) throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    private static Connection openConnection(String url) throws Exception {\n        JDBCDataSource dataSource = new JDBCDataSource();\n\n        dataSource.setUrl(url);\n        dataSource.setUser(\"SA\");\n        dataSource.setPassword(\"\");\n\n        return dataSource.getConnection();\n    }\n\n    private static void writeAndReadLobBlock(Database database, byte[] expectedBlock) {\n        LobStoreRAFile lobStore = new LobStoreRAFile(database, expectedBlock.length);\n\n        lobStore.setBlockBytes(expectedBlock, 0, 1);\n\n        assertThat(lobStore.getBlockBytes(0, 1)).isEqualTo(expectedBlock);\n        lobStore.close();\n    }\n\n    private static Session databaseSession(Connection connection) throws Exception {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1595, "output": 2511, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalToke