[thinking] **Exploring class loading solutions**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I see that `RAFile` calls `Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().loadClass(cname)`. I could create a `ClassProvidingLoader` that extends `ClassLoader` to return classes for storage. Is this normal? Yes, it is. Using it for the first write ensures success before hiding the loader for fallback. But if the original context loader can’t load, then a custom loader returning an already-loaded class will work. 
[thinking] 
